# Always use LF for source and config files so the `#!/usr/bin/env bun`
# shebang and shell scripts work under WSL/POSIX even when edited on Windows.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.png binary
*.ico binary
# Generated by `cargo about`; preserve crate license texts byte-for-byte
# (some bundle CRLF) so the rust-ci licenses diff against a fresh generation
# matches. Without -text, eol=lf normalization would strip those CRLFs.
rust/THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md -text linguist-generated
